reviews.review_text: I can't believe it was commercially released under the name "Rocking the Cradle" This is the ultimate trip!!! This show was recorded the day I was born. Seventeen years later I attended my first Dead concert at RFK Stadium in the Summer of 1995. I knew very little about the band at the time but fell in love with the music, the lot, and the entire scene very quickly. It wasn't until I discovered Archive that I found out they had performed on the day I was born. This is an excellent concert and it occurred under a lunar eclipse!!! Trippy!!! I wish I could have witnessed it. I bet it was an incredible experience.  I'd like to thank any and everyone who made it possible for me to hear this. The Grateful Dead for so freely allowing the recording and distribution of their concerts. To the person who recorded it and to Archive for hosting it. Thank you all!!! This show is absolutely awesome!!!
